# macOS
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store

# Digitization intermediates — operator ruling 2026-07-16: these carry source
# expression (copyrighted 1970s text) and are local-only working substrate,
# never part of the public distro. This supersedes the charter's Stage A
# "committed intermediate" language: the intermediate is still the single
# thing everything downstream reads, and is still content-hash-verified —
# it is just not published. The public repo carries ONLY what ships:
# schemas, corpus entries (mechanics + firewalled expression), manifests,
# edge changelogs, findings.
#
# Layout (2026-07-18 restructure): the published schema-corpora live under
# system/<work>/ (git carries these); the digitization substrate lives under
# a SEPARATE top-level digitization/<work>/ tree (gitignored below). Tooling
# takes --work <name> and resolves digitization/<name>/{pages,transcripts}.
/digitization/
**/digitization/

# Belt-and-braces: no source scans or PDFs ever land in the public repo.
*.pdf
**/sources/

# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/

# Editor
*.swp
*~
